init_text:
Is It Wrong to Focus on Animal Welfare When Humans Are Suffering?

Would you be surprised to hear that a study found that research subjects were more upset by stories of a dog beaten by a baseball bat than of an adult similarly beaten? Or that other researchers found that if forced to choose, 40 percent of people would save their pet dog over a foreign tourist.

Why do you think many people are more empathetic toward the suffering of animals than that of people? In your opinion, is it wrong to focus on animal welfare when humans are suffering? Why do you think so?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: it is wrong to focus on the suffering of animals when humans are suffering.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I believe that humans are the paramount species on this planet, and that any attempts to divert our efforts toward improving the welfare of animals is entirely counterproductive.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Regarding the first of the questions, consider that research subjects who were asked about animal suffering were distressed by stories about a dog being beaten with a

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: baseball bat yet did not feel disturbed about an adult being beaten with a similar weapon.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The same is true with humans: the majority of humans are being beaten with "baseball bats" such as oppression, poverty, and injustice.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When will we begin to feel upset about people who are beaten with baseball bats?

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: When will we begin to feel upset about people who are beaten with baseball bats?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Also, stories about animal abuse are much more visual.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Stories about human suffering usually include statistics that have little emotional appeal.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Images of abused animals, on the other hand are much more visceral.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I can still easily conjure up the picture of a cow on its knees in a slaughterhouse, its tongue forced down its throat, when I compare

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: that to the outline of a human in my head, all I see is a blob.
